There are three requests needed to update a issue type avatar (upload, crop, confirm). Session cookies need to be preserved between the first two requests. I believe this is true of other types of avatars as well.

Atlassian Connect add-ons (and any other automated solution that uses this API) would benefit from a single-request alternative that takes a pre-cropped image and cuts out the temporary step, without the need for handling cookies.

Also, the [rest docs|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/latest/#d2e1131] seem to get the last step a bit wrong. The {{PUT}} request should be to {{http://localhost:8090/jira/rest/api/2/issuetype/1/}} not to {{http://localhost:8090/jira/rest/api/2/issuetype/1/avatar}} and the {{id}} of the 2nd response's payload needs to be translated to {{avatarId}} in the 3rd request's payload.

